About this Item

Plate : 'Mariage de l'Empereur Napoleon III'. This plate shows the marriage of Louis-Napoleon Bonaparte (1808 - 1873), the first President of the French Second Republic and, as Napoleon III, the Emperor of the Second French Empire. Engraving on a vellin type paper. Description: This original antique print was published ca. 1850.Artists and Engravers: This plate by Follet after Philippoteaux. Condition: Good. General age-related toning and light staining. Print has been in matting, some discolouring on print. Please study scan carefully. Storage location: (RCTPC) C284-33 The overall size is ca. 6.1 x 9.1 inch. The image size is ca. 3.7 x 6.1 inch. The overall size is ca. 15.5 x 23 cm. The image size is ca. 9.5 x 15.5 cm.
